    "long_instructions": "## Do This\r\n\r\n1. In your `custom.py` file create a function called `navigate_path` that moves the `Painter` forward until it can no longer move.\r\n    - Hint: Use a `while` loop and a `can_move()` method to set a direction for the `Painter`.\r\n2. Use the `navigate_path()` function inside a loop to navigate through The Neighborhood.\r\n    - Hint: Remember to use the `turn_left()` `Painter` method and `turn_right()` function as needed.\r\n    \r\n**Reminder:** Make sure you import your `custom.py` file and save it to your backpack after adding any new functions!\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## AI Tutor Support:\r\n\r\n::: details [**Not sure how to move until the `Painter` reaches an obstacle?**]\r\n\r\n**Ask AI:**\r\n- How do I use a while loop to make my `Painter` move until it reaches a wall?\r\n- What happens if I don’t check `can_move()` before calling move()?\r\n:::\r\n\r\n\r\n::: details [**Stuck on navigation?**]\r\n\r\n**Ask AI:**\r\n- How do I decide when to turn my `Painter`?\r\n- How can I use `navigate_path()` multiple times in my program?\r\n:::",
